<paragraph id="7C4D0034CF4ACD1006D9FB57B62DB67A" blockId="1.[151,1437,1106,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1006D9FB57B1B7B4BF" box="[199,665,1250,1275]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" reason="1">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1006D9FB57B2FDB4BF" bold="true" box="[199,467,1250,1275]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnostic description</emphasis>
(based on male).
</emphasis>
Eyes medium (1/5 to 1/3 head length). 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10027DFB56B7F9B4BF" box="[1123,1239,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Antenna 1</emphasis>
short, not longer than article 4 of antenna 2 peduncle. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10042AFAB3B188B55A" box="[564,678,1286,1310]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Antenna 2</emphasis>
peduncular articles well developed, incrassate; peduncular article 3 without ventral process. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1007B2FA9EB12BB507" box="[428,517,1323,1347]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Labrum</emphasis>
with robust setae. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1004C7FA9EB06AB507" box="[729,836,1323,1347]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Mandible</emphasis>
left lacinia mobilis 5-dentate. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100283FA9EB638B507" box="[1181,1302,1323,1347]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Maxilliped</emphasis>
palp article 2 distomedial lobe well developed; article 4 reduced, button-shaped. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1005B3FAFBB76BB523" bold="true" box="[941,1093,1358,1383]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Gnathopod 1</emphasis>
sub or parachelate; 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100331FAFBB063B5CF" bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">posterior margin of propodus with lobe covered in palmate setae</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10057EFAC6B0D6B5CF" box="[864,1016,1395,1419]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Gnathopod 2</emphasis>
subchelate; merus and carpus free; dactylus not modified distally. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1007ECFA23B1B5B5EA" box="[498,667,1430,1454]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Pereopods 3–7</emphasis>
cuspidactylate. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10054EFA23B0D6B5EA" box="[848,1016,1430,1454]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Pereopods 5–7</emphasis>
without setae along posterior margin of the dactylus. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100752FA0FB1CCB597" bold="true" box="[332,738,1466,1491]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100752FA0FB2DBB597" bold="true" box="[332,501,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Pereopods 6–7</emphasis>
sexually dimorphic
</emphasis>
, without row of short setae along posterior margin of dactyli. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100689FA6BB21CB5B2" box="[151,306,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Pleonites 1–3</emphasis>
without dorsal spines. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100423FA6BB18BB5B2" box="[573,677,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Pleopods</emphasis>
all well developed. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100591FA6AB0C1B5B2" box="[911,1007,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Epimera</emphasis>
without vertical slits. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1002EFFA6BB671B5B3" bold="true" box="[1265,1375,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Uropod 1</emphasis>
rami without apical spear-shaped setae; outer ramus slender; 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100507F9B7B74EB65F" bold="true" box="[793,1120,1538,1563]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">with marginal robust setae</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10026EF9B6B7F0B65F" box="[1136,1246,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Uropod 3</emphasis>
well developed; ramus subequal to or longer than peduncle. 
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10049FF993B1E7B67A" box="[641,713,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Telson</emphasis>
apically incised, with 7–10+ robust setae per lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="34E853BFCF4ACD1006D9F9FEB253B7E3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7C4D0034CF4ACD1006D9F9FEB048B6B6" blockId="1.[151,1437,1106,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1006D9F9FEB215B627" bold="true" box="[199,315,1611,1635]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
A number of taxa in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD1004ABF9FEB064B627" authorityName="Serejo &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2008" box="[693,842,1611,1635]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1004ABF9FEB064B627" box="[693,842,1611,1635]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Bellorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are still poorly known. 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD10027BF9FEB215B6C2" authority="(Hurley, 1956)" baseAuthorityName="Hurley" baseAuthorityYear="1956" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chathamensis">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10027BF9FEB6B5B627" box="[1125,1435,1611,1635]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Bellorchestia chathamensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18637DC5CF4ACD100680F9DBB21DB6C2" author="Hurley, D. E." box="[158,307,1646,1670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="359 - 389" refId="ref13874" refString="Hurley, D. E. (1956) Studies on the New Zealand amphipodan fauna. No. 13. Sandhoppers of the genus Talorchestia. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 84, 359 - 389." type="journal article" year="1956">Hurley, 1956</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
should be placed in a new genus mainly because it has a well developed palmate lobe on the carpus of male gnathopod 2. 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD10078CF926B03FB6EE" authority="(Hurley, 1956)" baseAuthorityName="Hurley" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[402,785,1682,1707]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirki">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10078CF926B14CB6EF" box="[402,610,1683,1707]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Bellorchestia kirki</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18637DC5CF4ACD10046DF927B027B6EE" author="Hurley, D. E." box="[627,777,1682,1706]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="359 - 389" refId="ref13874" refString="Hurley, D. E. (1956) Studies on the New Zealand amphipodan fauna. No. 13. Sandhoppers of the genus Talorchestia. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 84, 359 - 389." type="journal article" year="1956">Hurley, 1956</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is poorly described. It remains in 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD100285F926B601B6EF" authorityName="Serejo &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2008" box="[1179,1327,1683,1707]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100285F926B601B6EF" box="[1179,1327,1683,1707]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Bellorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on Hurley’s indications that it is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD10048DF902B02FB68A" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[659,769,1718,1742]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tumida">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10048DF902B02FB68A" box="[659,769,1718,1742]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">B. tumida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other taxa, such as 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD1005EEF902B662B68A" authority="(Haswell, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Haswell" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1008,1356,1718,1742]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1005EEF902B7A0B68A" box="[1008,1166,1719,1742]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">B. marmorata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18637DC5CF4ACD100280F903B66DB68A" author="Haswell, W. A." box="[1182,1347,1718,1742]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="97 - 105" refId="ref13832" refString="Haswell, W. A. (1880) On some new amphipods from Australia and Tasmania. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, 5 (1), 97 - 105, pls 5 - 7." type="journal article" year="1880">Haswell, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD10039AF902B2CEB6B6" authority="(Haswell, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Haswell" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pravidactyla">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10039AF902B20BB6B7" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">B. pravidactyla</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18637DC5CF4ACD10072DF96FB2F9B6B6" author="Haswell, W. A." box="[307,471,1754,1778]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="97 - 105" refId="ref13832" refString="Haswell, W. A. (1880) On some new amphipods from Australia and Tasmania. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, 5 (1), 97 - 105, pls 5 - 7." type="journal article" year="1880">Haswell, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
are badly in need of redescription.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C4D0034CF4ACD1006D9F94BB253B7E3" blockId="1.[151,1437,1106,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD1006D9F94BB275B752" authorityName="Serejo &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2008" box="[199,347,1790,1814]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1006D9F94BB275B752" box="[199,347,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Bellorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs in the 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD100413F94BB154B752" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[525,634,1790,1814]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Orchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD100413F94BB154B752" box="[525,634,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Orchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of talitrids (
<bibRefCitation id="18637DC5CF4ACD10054DF94BB743B752" author="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Coleman, C. O." box="[851,1133,1790,1814]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="64 - 68" refId="ref14015" refString="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Coleman, C. O. (2012) A new terrestrial talitrid genus from the Philippine Islands (Crustacea, Amphipoda, Talitrida, Talitridae) and the designation of two informal subgroups. Zootaxa, 3400, 64 - 68." type="journal article" year="2012">Lowry &amp; Coleman 2012</bibRefCitation>
) that contains genera with robust setae on the outer ramus of uropod 1, a 5-dentate lacinia mobilis and more that 7 robust setae on each lobe of the telson. However, robust setae on the labrum of the upper lip, a palmate lobe only on the propodus of male gnathopod 1 and sexually dimorphic pereopods 6–7, makes it is difficult to align 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD10023FF8DEB79BB7C7" authorityName="Serejo &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2008" box="[1057,1205,1899,1923]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Bellorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD10023FF8DEB79BB7C7" box="[1057,1205,1899,1923]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Bellorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with other genera in the 
<taxonomicName id="BBF27BB7CF4ACD1006DEF83BB203B7E2" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[192,301,1934,1958]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Orchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E86DC26CF4ACD1006DEF83BB203B7E2" box="[192,301,1934,1958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Orchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
